Name: Wapen van Londen
Review Text: Extremely cosy bar nestled on the Amstel, very close to Rembrandtplein.  Shon and his team offer a great selection of Czech and Eastern European beers, a delicious beef Goulash, pierogi and Polish sausages in brine.  A great chill place!

Name: Wapen van Londen
Review Text: A little bit of Slovak/Czech in Amsterdam style. Small bar but fine. But very expensive beer for what you maybe are used to pay for in Slovakia or Czech. For example a zlaty bazant costs you here about 6 euro! So don't  expect Slovakia or Czech prizes. It's normal to pay 6 euro for 0.5l of beer in Amsterdam.
